is he free to be and do what he wants. While a strong reflection of the time at which it was written, <em>Owls Do Cry</em> remains innovative and relevant. Frame’s idiosyncratic and startlingly visual style means that the book’s immense power to unnerve, astonish and impress endures.</p> <p>• To order <em>Owls Do Cry</em> for £7.19 (RRP £8.99) go to <a href=\"http://bookshop.theguardian.com/catalog/product/view/id/360240/?utm_source=editoriallink&amp;utm_medium=merch&amp;utm_campaign=article\" title=\"\">bookshop.theguardian.com</a> or call 0330 333 6846. Free UK p&amp;p over £10, online orders only. Phone orders min p&amp;p of £1.99.</p>","liveBloggingNow":"false","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/4gjf4","wordcount":"228","thumbnail":"http://media.guim.co.uk/4ccf9250a4c1f6f2564295159d7609d539093199/0_0_2355_1414/140.jpg","commentCloseDate":"2016-03-25T17:37:00Z","standfirst":"The modernist masterpiece about siblings struggling with money, health and grief still has the power to unnerve and astonish nearly 60 years after it was first published"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/feb/11/owls-do-cry-janet-frame-review-new-zealand-s-first-big-novel","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/books/2016/feb/11/owls-do-cry-janet-frame-review-new-zealand-s-first-big-novel","sectionName":"Books","elements":[{"id":"4ccf9250a4c1f6f2564295159d7609d539093199","relation":"main","type":"image","assets":[{"type":"image","file":"http://media.guim.co.uk/4ccf9250a4c1f6f2564295159d7609d539093199/0_0_2355_1414/2000.jpg","typeData":{"copyright":"Ronald Grant Archive","picdarUrn":"GD*7816946","mediaApiUri":"https://api.media.gutools.co.uk/images/4ccf9250a4c1f6f2564295159d7609d539093199","suppliersReference":"AN ANGEL AT MY TAB#1.jpg","altText":"Jane Campion’s 1990 film of Frame’s life, An Angel at My Table ","caption":"Jane Campion’s 1990 film of Frame’s life, <em>An Angel at My Table. </em>","source":"Ronald Grant","credit":"Photograph: Ronald Grant","mediaId":"4ccf9250a4c1f6f25