a-media-id=\"d670f3192c1cc937ce7ab7c2918992d2d65741b6\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/d670f3192c1cc937ce7ab7c2918992d2d65741b6/0_0_910_900/910.jpg\" alt=\"SuperHappyMagicForest cover\" width=\"910\" height=\"900\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Illustrated books category: </strong><strong>Super Happy Magic Forest by Matty Long (Oxford University Press)</strong><br>When the Mystical Crystals of Life are stolen, five brave heroes must go on an epic quest to get them back and save the Super Happy Magic Forest from the root of all evil.</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"f8b2f2879e233af952315b7d53a5f708d73111ec\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/f8b2f2879e233af952315b7d53a5f708d73111ec/0_0_3532_4080/866.jpg\" alt=\"Illustrated books category: Cinderella’s Sister and the Big Bad Wolf by Lorraine Carey and Migy Blanco (Nosy Crow)\" width=\"866\" height=\"1000\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Illustrated books category: Cinderella’s Sister and the Big Bad Wolf by Lorraine Carey and Migy Blanco (Nosy Crow) </strong><br>A different take on a classic fairy tale, Cinderella’s Sister and the Big Bad Wolf tells the story of Cinderella’s heretofore unknown third ‘Ugly’ sister, Gertie. Gertie dreams of going to the ball but her mother and sisters insist she is much too nice. Gertie sets out on a quest to become bad, but this turns out to be much harder than it sounds. <br></span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"7061b94686ad836d9acbc3afe592834b579a9858\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/7061b94686ad836d9acbc3afe592834b579a9858/0_0_3317_3012/1000.jpg\" alt=\"Hector and Hummingbird  by Nicholas John Frith (Alison Green Books)\" width=\"1000\" height=\"908\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Illustrated books category: </strong><strong>Hector and Hummingbird by Nicholas John Frith (Alison Green Books)</strong><br>Hector and Hummingbird is the story of an unlikely friendship between a noisy hummingbird and a bear who just wants to find peace and quiet. When Hector finally stomps off to be alone however, he finds that life isn’t complete without his noisy friend.</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"918fe76e54eacf6f6134db3f2a640f9f0dc24e20\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/918fe76e54eacf6f6134db3f2a640f9f0dc24e20/0_0_2599_3531/736.jpg\" alt=\"The Bear and the Piano by David Litchfield (Frances Lincoln)\" width=\"736\" height=\"1000\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Illustrated books category: </strong><strong>The Bear and the Piano by David Litchfield (Frances Lincoln)</strong><br>One day, a young bear stumbles upon something he has never seen before in the forest. As time passes, he teaches himself how to play the strange instrument. Fame and fortune follow, but he misses the friends and family he has left behind.</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"deee989d4bd64d0476ceeb2c6afe589d66ec9960\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/deee989d4bd64d0476ceeb2c6afe589d66ec9960/0_0_2665_3262/817.jpg\" alt=\"Illustrated books category: Have You Seen Elephant? by David Barrow (Gecko Press)\" width=\"817\" height=\"1000\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Illustrated books category: Have You Seen Elephant? by David Barrow (Gecko Press) </strong><br>A young boy whiles away the hours at home by playing a game of hide and seek against the most challenging opponent he can imagine – an elephant.</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"a82d501b4f40a87944b75aa42c49ae0cea9829a0\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/a82d501b4f40a87944b75aa42c49ae0cea9829a0/0_0_748_864/433.jpg\" alt=\"The Crow’s Tale  by Naomi Howarth (Frances Lincoln)\" width=\"433\" height=\"500\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Illustrated books category: </strong><strong>The Crow’s Tale by Naomi Howarth (Frances Lincoln)</strong><br>In the dark depths of winter, snow is falling and the animals are freezing and famished. Brave Crow sets out on a dangerous journey to find the Sun, and beg for warmth.</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"4bf668eca4e0672d6fe030ea6465952b026cca15\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/4bf668eca4e0672d6fe030ea6465952b026cca15/0_0_3075_4700/654.jpg\" alt=\"My Brother is a Superhero by David Solomons (Nosy Crow)\" width=\"654\" height=\"1000\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Younger fiction category: </strong><strong>My Brother is a Superhero by David Solomons (Nosy Crow)</strong><br>Luke is a comic-mad 11-year-old who shares a treehouse with his geeky older brother, Zack. Luke’s only mistake is to go for a wee just at the wrong time. While he’s gone, an alien gives his undeserving, never-read-a-comic-in-his-life brother superpowers and then tells him to save the universe. Luke is massively annoyed about this, but when Zack is kidnapped by his arch-nemesis, Luke and his friends have only five days to find him and save the world.</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"51615a7ce563d6991bddd418f92cd7272dad75e1\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/51615a7ce563d6991bddd418f92cd7272dad75e1/0_0_669_945/354.jpg\" alt=\"Witch War  by Sibéal Pounder (Bloomsbury)\" width=\"354\" height=\"500\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Younger fiction category: </strong><strong>Witch War by Sibéal Pounder (Bloomsbury)</strong><br>When Fran the Fabulous Fairy turns up in Tiga Whicabim’s shed to tell her she’s a witch, Tiga doesn’t believe her. At least not until Fran points out that TIGA WHICABIM is actually an anagram of I AM A BIG WITCH and magics her away down the drainpipes to compete in Witch Wars – the competition to crown the next Top Witch of Ritzy City.</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"344c805110736bb8d3014cdda51dc37e8b15f7c9\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/344c805110736bb8d3014cdda51dc37e8b15f7c9/0_0_1525_2341/651.jpg\" alt=\"Bird by Crystal Chan (Tamarind)\" width=\"651\" height=\"1000\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Younger fiction category: </strong><strong>Bird by Crystal Chan (Tamarind)</strong><br>12-year-old Jewel never knew her brother, but all her life she has lived in his shadow. Then one night, on her birthday, she finds a mysterious boy sitting in her oak tree. His name is John. And he changes everything.</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"164250ee0157cdf63aecb8585ef7a34096308be7\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/164250ee0157cdf63aecb8585ef7a34096308be7/0_0_610_936/326.jpg\" alt=\"The Mystery of the Clockwork Sparrow  by Katherine Woodfine (Egmont)\" width=\"326\" height=\"500\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Younger fiction category: </strong><strong>The Mystery of the Clockwork Sparrow by Katherine Woodfine (Egmont)</strong><br>After the death of her father, Miss Sophie Taylor must seek employment. She’s thrilled to join the staff at Sinclair’s, the most beautiful department store in London. Sophie makes new friends: glamorous aspiring actress, Lil, serial paper obsessed Billy, and Joe – who is on the run from underworld criminals. When the priceless Clockwork Sparrow is stolen from Sinclair’s grand opening exhibition, it is up to Sophie and her friends to bring the dastardly villains to justice…</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"6a5ca76253721d63490f219c2bd9e30b6b50fb14\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/6a5ca76253721d63490f219c2bd9e30b6b50fb14/0_0_1500_2414/621.jpg\" alt=\"Darkmouth by Shane Hegarty (HarperCollins)\" width=\"621\" height=\"1000\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Younger fiction category: </strong><strong>Darkmouth by Shane Hegarty (HarperCollins)</strong><br>Legends (also known as terrifying, human-eating monsters) have invaded the town of Darkmouth and aim to conquer the world. The last remaining Legend Hunter - Finn - must protect us. But Finn is 12-years-old, loves animals, and isn’t a natural fighter.</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"d96c46bbe254352071edca68806511cedb751680\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/d96c46bbe254352071edca68806511cedb751680/0_0_1526_2339/652.jpg\" alt=\"The Blackthorn Key by Kevin Sands (Puffin)\" width=\"652\" height=\"1000\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Younger fiction category: </strong><strong>The Blackthorn Key by Kevin Sands (Puffin)</strong><br>London 1665. 14-year-old Christopher Rowe is apprenticed to master apothecary Benedict Blackthorn. It is a dangerous time to be an apothecary’s apprentice – the sinister Cult of the Archangel is prowling the streets of London, targeting apothecaries in a wave of mysterious murders. When the trail of violence leads back to Blackthorn’s shop, Christopher finds himself on the run with a coded message about his master’s most dangerous, secret project and the cryptic warning: “Tell no one!”</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"102db71f12fafb47107acbe9e116d6b8d871929a\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/102db71f12fafb47107acbe9e116d6b8d871929a/0_0_1500_2339/641.jpg\" alt=\"The Art of Being Normal  by Lisa Williamson (David Fickling)\" width=\"641\" height=\"1000\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Older fiction category: </strong><strong>The Art of Being Normal by Lisa Williamson (David Fickling)</strong><br>Two outsiders. Two secrets. David longs to be a girl. Leo wants to be invisible. When Leo stands up for David in a fight, an unlikely friendship forms. But things are about to get messy. Because at Eden Park School secrets have a funny habit of not staying secret for long…</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"4e06b69998512ccecdc932570ecf90f8bb3358a8\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/4e06b69998512ccecdc932570ecf90f8bb3358a8/0_0_1525_2337/653.jpg\" alt=\"I’ll Give You the Sun by Jandy Nelson (Walker)\" width=\"653\" height=\"1000\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Older fiction category: </strong><strong>I’ll Give You the Sun by Jandy Nelson (Walker)</strong><br>Jude and her twin Noah were incredibly close – until a tragedy drove them apart. Now they are barely speaking – and both falling for boys they can’t have. What the twins don’t realise is that each of them has only half the story and if they can just find their way back to one another, they have a chance to remake their world.</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"c36a7d1f416ef7545262c4f524f6cf9cf7ab9450\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/c36a7d1f416ef7545262c4f524f6cf9cf7ab9450/0_0_1524_2339/652.jpg\" alt=\"The Sin Eater’s Daughter  by Melinda Salisbury (Scholastic)\" width=\"652\" height=\"1000\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Older fiction category: </strong><strong>The Sin Eater’s Daughter by Melinda Salisbury (Scholastic) </strong><br> 17-year-old Twylla has a gift – or a curse: she can kill with a single touch. Now not only is she to marry the prince, but she must be court executioner, compelled to do the queen’s bidding. When she meets a rebellious guard however, Twylla starts to question everything she’s been told. The queen has a plan to destroy her enemies, a plan that requires a stomach-churning, unthinkable sacrifice. Will Twylla do what it takes to protect her kingdom? Or will she abandon her duty in favour of a doomed love?</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"ba652438c45ef9fe3a069456b338402baf4205fb\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/ba652438c45ef9fe3a069456b338402baf4205fb/0_0_456_700/326.jpg\" alt=\"Seed by Lisa Heathfield (Egmont)\" width=\"326\" height=\"500\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Older fiction category: </strong><strong>Seed by Lisa Heathfield (Egmont)</strong><br>15-year-old Pearl has lived her whole life protected within the small community at Seed, where they worship Nature and idolise their leader, Papa S. When a family of outsiders joins their community, everything changes. Pearl experiences feelings she never knew existed: uncertainty, hesitation, fear. She begins to see that there is darkness at the heart of Seed. A darkness she must escape from before it’s too late.</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"68ff63796848dbeee89c9242b39a50258b02d1f1\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/68ff63796848dbeee89c9242b39a50258b02d1f1/0_0_1525_2340/652.jpg\" alt=\"The Accident Season by Moïra Fowley-Doyle (Corgi)\" width=\"652\" height=\"1000\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Older fiction category: </strong><strong>The Accident Season by Moïra Fowley-Doyle (Corgi)</strong><br>It’s the accident season, the same time every year. Bones break, skin tears, bruises bloom. The accident season has been part of 17-year-old Cara’s life for as long as she can remember. Towards the end of October, foreshadowed by the deaths of many relatives before them, Cara’s family becomes inexplicably accident-prone. But why are they so cursed? And how can they break free?</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"6adaac1a1685805882e5cdc1f69f0a38268e14ad\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/6adaac1a1685805882e5cdc1f69f0a38268e14ad/0_0_1521_2339/650.jpg\" alt=\"13 Days of Midnight  by Leo Hunt (Orchard)\" width=\"650\" height=\"1000\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Older fiction category: </strong><strong>13 Days of Midnight by Leo Hunt (Orchard)</strong><br>When Luke Manchett’s estranged father dies suddenly, he leaves his son a dark inheritance. Little does Luke know that alongside the million pounds, books and mysterious rings he has inherited, he has also been left in charge of his father’s ghost collection: eight restless spirits. They want revenge for their long enslavement. With the help of his new friend Elza Moss, and his cowardly dog Ham, Luke has just thirteen days to uncover the closely guarded secrets of black magic, and send the unquiet spirits to their eternal rest.</span> </figcaption> </figure>","liveBloggingNow":"false","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/4gtb2","wordcount":"0","thumbnail":"http://media.guim.co.uk/6a5ca76253721d63490f219c2bd9e30b6b50fb14/59_154_1365_819/140.jpg","standfirst":"<p>Discover the shortlists for the three categories of the Waterstones children’s book prize 2016 - illustrated books, younger fiction, older fiction - where six books compete within each category to be crowned category winner, with the three category winners then vying for the overall title of Waterstones Children’s Book of the Year 2016. The winners will be announced on Thursday 17 March</p>"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/childrens-books-site/gallery/2016/feb/11/waterstones-childrens-book-prize-2016-shortlists-in-pictures","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/childrens-books-site/gallery/2016/feb/1